# 

<span key="ce4a4a1e9f9b4ddca1114f857f8b2a78"><span offset-key="ce4a4a1e9f9b4ddca1114f857f8b2a78:0">The UX Engineer Role</span></span>

<span key="7db05a4a6d194d36a783e0b2510e1851"><span offset-key="7db05a4a6d194d36a783e0b2510e1851:0">Congratulations! For the next 4â€“8 sprints, you're a </span>**UX Engineer**<span offset-key="7db05a4a6d194d36a783e0b2510e1851:2"> ðŸŽ‰</span></span>

<span key="afad88493c6e4769a1216f34b1f44073"><span offset-key="afad88493c6e4769a1216f34b1f44073:0">As a UX Engineer, you'll serve as the design lead for your team. You'll work to set the vision and direction for your team's user interface and experience (UI/UX) work. You'll craft design planning artifacts like user flows and wireframes, then generate tickets for your product's design backlog to drive development. You'll also work closely with your TPM(s) to scope realistic design goals for each sprint, and then with frontend engineers to implement your plan and achieve them.</span></span>

<span key="66e284d8dad64d02937f88383d397522"><span offset-key="66e284d8dad64d02937f88383d397522:0">As a UX Engineer, you'll be directly responsible for:</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="c276980e5f5b45a8acaf28470481cbe6"><span offset-key="c276980e5f5b45a8acaf28470481cbe6:0">Communicating the UI/UX vision to your TPM(s) and your team.</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="ad750c7683ad41ff8aa33632aa48ae59"><span offset-key="ad750c7683ad41ff8aa33632aa48ae59:0">Generating and maintaining design artifacts (including user flows and wireframes) to plan and document UI/UX.</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="4f0f38370bd046f69723bb1b71d65d42"><span offset-key="4f0f38370bd046f69723bb1b71d65d42:0">Working to generate, prioritize, and achieve shippable implementation of tickets in your product's design backlog.</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="354cd4a032ea403a99a75a6e4ac5970e"><span offset-key="354cd4a032ea403a99a75a6e4ac5970e:0">Crafting UI components and data visualizations alongside frontend developers and data scientists on your team and product.</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="831f76df56034f6ebc3d82731b4e1caf"><span offset-key="831f76df56034f6ebc3d82731b4e1caf:0">Representing UI/UX progress and vision in product reviews and stakeholder meetings.</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="44ee4b98e50247efa2273cb0dfb872b1"><span offset-key="44ee4b98e50247efa2273cb0dfb872b1:0">Working under the direction of the Design Manager to push your team to follow best practices for developing modern user interfaces.</span></span>

# 

<span key="7a2988b29ce04d5fbe4a5c25f9a6a9fa"><span offset-key="7a2988b29ce04d5fbe4a5c25f9a6a9fa:0">Your Objectives</span></span>

<span key="b369046dbf444df1b037be898dddd76b"><span offset-key="b369046dbf444df1b037be898dddd76b:0">Throughout Labs, your goal is to </span>**work toward your objectives**<span offset-key="b369046dbf444df1b037be898dddd76b:2">.</span></span>

<span key="8b6fb3a3e8cd4209af736d67ecfcb597"><span offset-key="8b6fb3a3e8cd4209af736d67ecfcb597:0">You can track your progress in your </span>**Objectives course in Canvas**<span offset-key="8b6fb3a3e8cd4209af736d67ecfcb597:2">. There, you'll also find a sprint-by-sprint breakdown suggesting a path to achieve all your objectives in four sprints.</span></span>

<span key="1b0138add8f24318acc507b6dceef2ac"><span offset-key="1b0138add8f24318acc507b6dceef2ac:0">As a </span>**UX Engineer**<span offset-key="1b0138add8f24318acc507b6dceef2ac:2">, here's what you'll need to achieve to pass Labs and graduate:</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="eef31773b5f442f0b0229322173fd336"><span offset-key="eef31773b5f442f0b0229322173fd336:0">\[ \] Attend at least two Stakeholder Meetings for your product</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="3b986242e8c341cc9a90361a8b2689a4"><span offset-key="3b986242e8c341cc9a90361a8b2689a4:0">\[ \] Attend at least four Product Reviews for your product</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="a3011fb2062e45f0b4d0604a88c63802"><span offset-key="a3011fb2062e45f0b4d0604a88c63802:0">\[ \] Attend at least four Design Critique sessions</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="0c1764fd9e474619ba88d3ee77acec99"><span offset-key="0c1764fd9e474619ba88d3ee77acec99:0">\[ \] Pass </span>`Labs`<span offset-key="0c1764fd9e474619ba88d3ee77acec99:2"> course</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="b6d730771d7c403c8bd96396002edbf8"><span offset-key="b6d730771d7c403c8bd96396002edbf8:0">\[ \] Pass </span>`Labs: UX Engineer`<span offset-key="b6d730771d7c403c8bd96396002edbf8:2"> course</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="b2cd8be0bf644a56b7e28bf499636b1a"><span offset-key="b2cd8be0bf644a56b7e28bf499636b1a:0">\[ \] Pass </span>`Career Readiness`<span offset-key="b2cd8be0bf644a56b7e28bf499636b1a:2"> course</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="55f0127d3dcf4441b1698fccece602a2"><span offset-key="55f0127d3dcf4441b1698fccece602a2:0">\[ \] Peer-review at least six teammates on Searchlight</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="c4851b665198473bb8885218de02a8f2"><span offset-key="c4851b665198473bb8885218de02a8f2:0">\[ \] Submit at least five qualified pull requests</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="53774e8d42254f39ad55f4e5e5a120ba"><span offset-key="53774e8d42254f39ad55f4e5e5a120ba:0">\[ \] Review at least 10 pull requests from your team</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="4e6c0c59da764322b97d409e8923eae5"><span offset-key="4e6c0c59da764322b97d409e8923eae5:0">\[ \] Have at least one pull request merged</span></span>

<span key="5235717b140946909a935d8f852ac729"><span offset-key="5235717b140946909a935d8f852ac729:0">For more information, visit </span></span><a href="https://docs.labs.lambdaschool.com" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="60ccfa8585e74d58b947adcd44ffc4f8" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-48487_259-48488-237__"><span data-key="471150c73d63412cb3db16a279e7aa23"><span data-offset-key="471150c73d63412cb3db16a279e7aa23:0">the Labs Docs (Links to an external site.)</span></span></span></a><span key="2cd43d02c240406d915ebc320436099c"><span offset-key="2cd43d02c240406d915ebc320436099c:0">!</span></span>

# 

<span key="ad90255995a045c88f1c92771923ef68"><span offset-key="ad90255995a045c88f1c92771923ef68:0">Design Tools in Labs</span></span>

<span key="1f5b3429e19f450195bd5c0b760fc515"><span offset-key="1f5b3429e19f450195bd5c0b760fc515:0">As a UX Engineer, you'll be using various industry tools to generate and maintain </span>**design artifacts**<span offset-key="1f5b3429e19f450195bd5c0b760fc515:2"> (things you create for use by your team).</span></span>

## 

<span key="61cbd746519044f19c9becb3283724f6"><span offset-key="61cbd746519044f19c9becb3283724f6:0">Whimsical</span></span>

<span key="b29fbdd347364569a5592b188c07a409"><span offset-key="b29fbdd347364569a5592b188c07a409:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">â€‹</span></span></span><a href="https://whimsical.com" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="38552eb3d76f469f9202fd9d59208ddd" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-48487_259-48488-237__"><span data-key="248757a70a194265989c7835885708e7"><span data-offset-key="248757a70a194265989c7835885708e7:0">Whimsical (Links to an external site.)</span></span></span></a><span key="02092d37fe7f402c84b535d924aa29b4"><span offset-key="02092d37fe7f402c84b535d924aa29b4:0"> is a diagramming and rapid prototyping tool you can use to create flowcharts, wireframes, mind maps, sticky notes, and docs.</span></span>

<span key="8b78386dc12a4dae8255e6ed29b3721a"><span offset-key="8b78386dc12a4dae8255e6ed29b3721a:0">You'll mostly use Whimsical to create </span>**user flows**<span offset-key="8b78386dc12a4dae8255e6ed29b3721a:2"> and </span>**wireframes**<span offset-key="8b78386dc12a4dae8255e6ed29b3721a:4">.</span></span>

<span key="487f0b1907304a48b6e1df04a0328eec">**User Flows**<span offset-key="487f0b1907304a48b6e1df04a0328eec:1"> are flowcharts showing a user's path through your productâ€”what decisions they make, actions they take, and what screens and features they use along the way. They provide a map (really, a graph) showing all the possible paths.</span></span>

<span key="5ab501bcb8ed4bcb9433aa225f4e63f8">**Wireframes**<span offset-key="5ab501bcb8ed4bcb9433aa225f4e63f8:1"> are quick, lightweight sketches of the basic layout of each page, view, or feature in your product.</span></span>

<span key="44d5dd6f1cce4b1fbdac067dfe7cd1ab"><span offset-key="44d5dd6f1cce4b1fbdac067dfe7cd1ab:0">Check out this quick overview of how Whimsical works:</span></span>

<span key="a3444b0c31764223a7eb69d30d637797"><span offset-key="a3444b0c31764223a7eb69d30d637797:0">Optionally, you can also find video tutorials for all of Whimsical's modes </span></span><a href="https://whimsical.com/whimsical-video-tutorials-Log31dDEDGwf65tBPf24fp" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="b1e4f283cd7145f38a2d6443008a3b5b" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-48487_259-48488-237__"><span data-key="4f1a191077b54dfcb0f3b2ac19cd2f63"><span data-offset-key="4f1a191077b54dfcb0f3b2ac19cd2f63:0">here (Links to an external site.)</span></span></span></a><span key="a8792ec9b1df4cfb8beb19a6777fcf7a"><span offset-key="a8792ec9b1df4cfb8beb19a6777fcf7a:0">!</span></span>

## 

<span key="4bcbc007ecf84ded9c8d9f79a8f1ac80"><span offset-key="4bcbc007ecf84ded9c8d9f79a8f1ac80:0">Figma</span></span>

<span key="ec975b5dc1cf4e61beb053dda9d13e5a"><span offset-key="ec975b5dc1cf4e61beb053dda9d13e5a:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">â€‹</span></span></span><a href="https://www.figma.com" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="14d79bc8fd1846e6a593bfef6d6d9b17" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-48487_259-48488-237__"><span data-key="d8e7bdf7f0b345e481a37fd681f6726e"><span data-offset-key="d8e7bdf7f0b345e481a37fd681f6726e:0">Figma (Links to an external site.)</span></span></span></a><span key="91dc025e18944d42ab0fb410c5c6d779"><span offset-key="91dc025e18944d42ab0fb410c5c6d779:0"> is a more feature-rich prototyping tool you can use to really dive deep into UI/UX possibilities for your product. You can use it to create detailed, interactive designs that incorporate not only how your product should look, but also how users will be able to use it.</span></span>

<span key="8098b47bf3214582b70c7e60b1a7abd1"><span offset-key="8098b47bf3214582b70c7e60b1a7abd1:0">Figma has a steeper learning curve than Whimsical, but you may still use it in Labs depending on your product.</span></span>

<span key="9a71dd662f3e49d28e7bc1bf31a7add1"><span offset-key="9a71dd662f3e49d28e7bc1bf31a7add1:0">If you'll be using Figma,</span></span><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Cx2dkpBxst8&amp;list=PLXDU_eVOJTx7QHLShNqIXL1Cgbxj7HlN4" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="cdc26ce066ec4479bf0b989c9fbbfccf" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-48487_259-48488-237__"><span data-key="dd7af8dbf79f403884aab624049d09f7"><span data-offset-key="dd7af8dbf79f403884aab624049d09f7:0">here's a useful playlist of tutorials (Links to an external site.)</span></span></span></a><span key="7145b158fc9a4bbb9920b4953070dbcc"><span offset-key="7145b158fc9a4bbb9920b4953070dbcc:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">â€‹</span></span></span>

UX\_TOPICS

<span key="d5bf2d29d74d4d5986030ad02112cf60"><span offset-key="d5bf2d29d74d4d5986030ad02112cf60:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">â€‹</span></span></span><a href="https://ant.design" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="092057c4593142dc86df9ebfc8dcb29b" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-48487_259-48488-237__"><span data-key="76a389975d8d40d99906e196a3afadb3"><span data-offset-key="76a389975d8d40d99906e196a3afadb3:0">Ant Design (Links to an external site.)</span></span></span></a><span key="87327b9736ec41c7970e84a0b73b51f1"><span offset-key="87327b9736ec41c7970e84a0b73b51f1:0"> is a UI framework encompassing a </span>**design system**<span offset-key="87327b9736ec41c7970e84a0b73b51f1:2"> and a </span>**component library**<span offset-key="87327b9736ec41c7970e84a0b73b51f1:4">. We'll dig into those terms more later! For now, know that almost every design element your team will need to use will be either available, composable, or adaptable from this library.</span></span>

<span key="019f92299b854d56b0f3ab90e3c6da2d"><span offset-key="019f92299b854d56b0f3ab90e3c6da2d:0">Your go-to for using Ant Design will be </span></span><a href="https://ant.design/docs/react/introduce" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="36fdd5e36c01479298ae1865771870b3" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-48487_259-48488-237__"><span data-key="95a6f05150564103b9ead51737038fd8"><span data-offset-key="95a6f05150564103b9ead51737038fd8:0">their official docs (Links to an external site.)</span></span></span></a><span key="f6aaaba3b8d445fe9aa05429da339f90"><span offset-key="f6aaaba3b8d445fe9aa05429da339f90:0">â€”you'll need to get comfortable reading through and referencing documentation to succeed on the job, so this design system should give you a lot of solid practice!</span></span>

<span key="901e6ad2627b4a85b19811deae893068"><span offset-key="901e6ad2627b4a85b19811deae893068:0">Now that you've got an overview of the tools you'll use in Labs, read on to learn about </span>**Design Critiques**<span offset-key="901e6ad2627b4a85b19811deae893068:2">.</span></span>
